<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF9E766EFF08D2154AD5F39A" blockId="67.[163,777,1612,1664]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFF08D2154B74F37B" box="[163,320,1612,1634]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
<typeStatus id="54A58873FF9E766EFF08D2154AEFF378" box="[163,219,1613,1634]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFEE5D2144AEEF39A" authority="van Helsdingen, 1985" authorityName="van Helsdingen" authorityYear="1985" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noordami">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFEE5D214480DF37B" box="[334,569,1612,1633]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Mitrager noordami</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FF9E766EFDE8D2144AEEF39A" author="Van Helsdingen PJ" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" pagination="353 - 358" refId="ref96869" refString="Van Helsdingen PJ. 1985. Mitrager noordami, an erigonine novelty from Java. Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society 6: 353 - 358." type="journal article" year="1985">van Helsdingen, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF9E766EFF08D2F24B82F201" blockId="67.[163,779,1705,1819]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFF08D2F24BA5F3A5" box="[163,401,1706,1727]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFE86D2F24BA5F3A5" authorityName="van Helsdingen" authorityYear="1985" box="[301,401,1706,1727]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mitrager</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is similar to other taxa on Clade 
<quantity id="4CE69B34FF9E766EFF08D2904AE8F3C4" box="[163,220,1736,1758]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.302" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" unit="in" value="13.0">13 in</quantity>
palpal and somatic features, but is characterized and can be distinguished by the following unique combination of features:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF9E766EFF1BD36C4F64F44C" blockId="67.[176,779,1844,1896]" lastBlockId="67.[832,1444,197,1200]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
1. Paracymbium: medium- to large-sized (small in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFF68D30A4B72F27D" box="[195,326,1874,1895]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFF68D30A4B72F27D" box="[195,326,1874,1895]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Oedothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); base not visible from dorsal view of male pedipalp (visible in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFB6AD49D4F70F5C0" box="[1217,1348,197,218]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFB6AD49D4F70F5C0" box="[1217,1348,197,218]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Oedothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); distal setae-bearing area not prominently laterally elevated (prominently laterally elevated in some 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFCF0D57949EBF42C" authorityName="Fage" authorityYear="1936" box="[859,991,289,310]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Callitrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFCF0D57949EBF42C" box="[859,991,289,310]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Callitrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); distal clasp with striae in many species (no striae in other taxa in Clade 13).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF9E766EFCEBD5074F3CF773" blockId="67.[832,1444,197,1200]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
2. Copulatory bulb: embolus base protuberance absent (present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFC5ED5254E4CF488" box="[1013,1144,381,402]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFC5ED5254E4CF488" box="[1013,1144,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Oedothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); embolus retrolaterally spiral (prolaterally spiral in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFB1BD5C44F07F4AB" box="[1200,1331,412,433]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFB1BD5C44F07F4AB" box="[1200,1331,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Oedothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), covered dorsally by lateral extension of radix (
<collectionCode id="ED0FAE14FF9E766EFA94D5E34F41F4CB" box="[1343,1397,443,465]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">LER</collectionCode>
) in most species, except 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFBF8D5824EE9F4F4" authorityName="COMB." authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Wunderlich" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1107,1245,473,495]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFBF8D5824E5EF4F5" box="[1107,1130,474,495]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFBD7D5814EE9F4F4" box="[1148,1245,473,494]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFAB4D5824FA8F4F4" baseAuthorityName="Tanasevitch" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[1311,1436,473,495]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tholusa">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFAB4D5824FA8F4F4" box="[1311,1436,473,495]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">M. tholusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which it is retrolateral to the embolus (LER absent in most other species in Clade 13 except 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFAD6D64F49F0F751" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2014" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Callitrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convector">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFAD6D64F49F0F751" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Ca. convector</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); tegular papillae absent (present in many 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFCF0D60C4E24F770" authority="and" authorityName="AND" box="[859,1040,596,618]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFCF0D60C49EAF773" box="[859,990,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Oedothorax</emphasis>
and
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFBBDD60C4ECDF773" baseAuthorityName="Locket &amp; Russell-Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[1046,1273,596,617]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Callitrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrophthalma">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFBBDD60C4ECDF773" box="[1046,1273,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Ca. macrophthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF9E766EFCEAD62B4EEFF667" blockId="67.[832,1444,197,1200]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
3. Palpal tibia: prolateral apophysis varies from small or absent to prominent in some species, but never elevated vertically except 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFB25D6E84F10F7DF" authorityName="van Helsdingen" authorityYear="1985" box="[1166,1316,688,709]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noordami">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFB25D6E84F10F7DF" box="[1166,1316,688,709]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">M. noordami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(vertically elevated in many 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFBB6D6964E95F7F9" authorityName="Fage" authorityYear="1936" box="[1053,1185,718,739]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Callitrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFBB6D6964E95F7F9" box="[1053,1185,718,739]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Callitrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); scaly prolateral spike present except 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFBACD6B64EADF618" authorityName="van Helsdingen" authorityYear="1985" box="[1031,1177,749,771]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noordami">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFBACD6B64EADF618" box="[1031,1177,749,771]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">M. noordami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, retrolaterally directed in most species (absent in other species in Clade 13); retrolateral apophysis short, retrolaterally curved in many species (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFB47D7114F97F645" authority="and" authorityName="AND" box="[1260,1443,841,863]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFB47D7114F5BF644" box="[1260,1391,841,862]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Oedothorax</emphasis>
and
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFCF0D73049EBF667" authorityName="Fage" authorityYear="1936" box="[859,991,872,893]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Callitrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFCF0D73049EBF667" box="[859,991,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Callitrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFB9ED7304EFFF667" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2014" box="[1077,1227,872,893]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Callitrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convector">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFB9ED7304EFFF667" box="[1077,1227,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Ca. convector</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF9E766EFCE8D7DE4E4FF1AA" blockId="67.[832,1444,197,1200]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
4. The general structure of the epigyne in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFA97D7DF4F97F686" authorityName="van Helsdingen" authorityYear="1985" box="[1340,1443,903,924]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFA97D7DF4F97F686" box="[1340,1443,903,924]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Mitrager</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely similar across species, and also similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFBC8D79C4EDFF6C3" authorityName="Fage" authorityYear="1936" box="[1123,1259,964,985]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Callitrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFBC8D79C4EDFF6C3" box="[1123,1259,964,985]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Callitrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFAACD79C4FA8F6C3" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2007" box="[1287,1436,964,985]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Holmelgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFAACD79C4FA8F6C3" box="[1287,1436,964,985]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Holmelgonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFCF0D7BA4E2AF6E2" authority="and" authorityName="AND" box="[859,1054,994,1016]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFCF0D7BA49D5F6ED" box="[859,993,994,1015]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Oedothorax</emphasis>
and
</taxonomicName>
other related taxa. It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFBEED0594EF9F10C" authorityName="Fage" authorityYear="1936" box="[1093,1229,1025,1046]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Callitrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFBEED0594EF9F10C" box="[1093,1229,1025,1046]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Callitrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFAA5D0594F97F10C" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2007" box="[1294,1443,1025,1046]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Holmelgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFAA5D0594F97F10C" box="[1294,1443,1025,1046]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Holmelgonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the position of the entrance of copulatory ducts into the spermathecae, more mesal to the exits of the fertilization ducts. For a general description of epigynal conformation, see shared features defining Clade 13 above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF9E766EFC90D0B14F90F060" blockId="67.[827,1444,1257,1402]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFC90D0B149F4F1E4" box="[827,960,1257,1278]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Monophyly:</emphasis>
This genus is supported by the following unambiguous character transformations: the retrolateral bending of palpal tibia prolateral spike (Ch 53, synapomorphic; lost in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFBC1D11E4EC8F040" authorityName="van Helsdingen" authorityYear="1985" box="[1130,1276,1349,1371]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noordami">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFBC1D11E4EC8F040" box="[1130,1276,1349,1371]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">M. noordami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the wavy prolateral margin of the embolus (Ch 14, homoplastic).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF9E766EFC90D1FB4F2DF3B4" blockId="67.[827,1443,1442,1710]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFC90D1FB49E0F0A2" box="[827,980,1443,1464]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Description:</emphasis>
The genus includes medium-sized erigonines mostly with a variegated opisthosoma. Male prosoma varies in degree of modification, ranging from unnoticeable (
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFC71D1A74E6DF309" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="1974" box="[986,1113,1534,1556]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFC71D1A74E6DF309" box="[986,1113,1534,1556]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">M. unicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFB25D1A74F37F309" authorityName="Lin &amp; Lopardo &amp; Uhl" authorityYear="2022" box="[1166,1283,1534,1556]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Callitrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFB25D1A74F37F309" box="[1166,1283,1534,1556]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">M. hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) to prominent post-PME humps, post-PME grooves, PME lobe, inter- AME-PME lobe, clypeal hump, cheliceral apophysis, pre-PME groove and modified setae. Chelicerae without mastidia. Clypeus with one sub-AME seta. For palpal and epigynal feature see diagnosis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF9E766EFC90D28F4EBEF233" blockId="67.[827,1442,1750,1834]" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFC90D28F4E38F3F1" box="[827,1036,1750,1772]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Species included:</emphasis>
This genus comprises 25 species (re-described below), among which 24 species are transferred from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF9E766EFC54D34C4EB6F233" box="[1023,1154,1812,1833]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="67" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFC54D34C4EB6F233" box="[1023,1154,1812,1833]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Oedothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF9E7669FC90D30A48B2F5E0" blockId="67.[827,1335,1874,1896]" lastBlockId="68.[145,760,197,250]" lastPageId="68" lastPageNumber="485" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF9E766EFC90D30A49F8F27D" box="[827,972,1874,1895]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F3097641FF9E766EFC72D30A4E2BF272" box="[985,1055,1874,1896]" name="Nepal" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3097641FF9E766EFB81D30A4E5CF272" box="[1066,1128,1874,1896]" name="India" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3097641FF9E766EFBDFD30A4ED0F272" box="[1140,1252,1874,1896]" name="Indonesia" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49DAF833FF9E766EFB58D30A4F1FF272" box="[1267,1323,1874,1896]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="67" pageNumber="484">Java</collectingRegion>
). 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF997669FF3AD49D4B61F5C0" box="[145,341,197,218]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="485">Natural history:</emphasis>
Most species have been collected from broad-leaved or coniferous forest litter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
